tool.name: LinearRef

param.name: query
param.displayname: Type of query to select records to modify?
param.dialogReference:
This option will allow you to set what type of query is run to linear reference the records.

  • ALL - all records in the database that have XY coords and spatial reference system defined

  • DATERANGE - records between two dates selected below

  • IDRANGE - records between two IDs selected below

param.name: over
param.dialogReference:
Clicking the checkbox will overwrite any exisiting transect distances (m value) for water quality records.

Leaving the box unchecked will only update any records that don't currently have a transect distance (m value).

param.name: date1
param.dialogReference: Begining date to update. Time does not matter.

param.name: date2
param.dialogReference: End date of range to update. Time does not matter.

param.name: id1
param.dialogReference:
Start water quality record ID to update.

Water quality record ID numbers can be found at water_quality.id

param.name: id2
param.dialogReference:
End water quality record ID to update.

Water quality record ID numbers can be found at water_quality.id

tool.summary:
WARNING: this tool can take a while to run when updating lots of records.

This tool will calculate the distance along the transect (m value) for each water quality record. It uses ArcGIS's linear referencing to locate the records along the transect route shapefile. The water quality record site must match the transect code in order to be linear referenced correctly.

Water quality records must have a XY location (x_coord, y_coord) and spatial reference (spatial_reference_code) set in the water_quality tables and must be located within 250m of the transect line.
